Representative McNeely
1 moves to amend the bill on page 26, line 50, through page 27, line 3, by rewriting those lines to
2 read:
3 "SECTION 9.2. Nothing in this section limits the ability of the City of Charlotte to
4 provide local funding for a project that (i) is eligible for State funding under G.S. 136-189.11 and
5 (ii) is not a highway project. The City of Charlotte may provide local funding participation for
6 a highway project eligible for funding under G.S. 136-189.11 in any amount, but notwithstanding
7 the provisions of G.S. 136-189.11(f), the Department of Transportation may not revise highway
8 project selection ratings based on local funding participation to the extent that it exceeds five
9 percent (5%) of the project cost.".
